-- German government is not considering eurobonds, spokesman says 
-- 
-- Wed Sep 03, 2014 08:07AM EDT
-- None



BERLIN, Sept 3 (Reuters) - The German government is not considering common euro zone bonds, a spokesman said on Wednesday after the head of Commerzbank <CBKG.DE> said such bonds would "permanently establish the euro as a globally important currency" and ensure European competitiveness.

